title: Pak Cuisines
text:
2.1 Zarda (Sweet Rice)






Zarda is a traditional Pakistani dessert made with sweet, fragrant rice cooked in milk, sugar, and spices like cardamom, saffron, and cinnamon. It’s often flavored with rose water or kewra (screw pine essence) and garnished with nuts like almonds or pistachios.

title: Pak Cuisines
text:
2.2 Kheer






Kheer is a classic Pakistani dessert similar to a rice pudding. It’s made with milk, sugar, and rice cooked together with spices like cardamom, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Kheer can be flavored with various ingredients like saffron, rose water, or nuts, and is often served chilled.

title: Pak Cuisines
text:
2.3 Halwa

 Halwa is a traditional Pakistani dessert made with flour, sugar, and ghee.

title: Pak Cuisines
text:
2.4 Sawaiyan






Sawaiyan is a traditional Pakistani dessert made with vermicelli noodles cooked in milk, sugar, and spices like cardamom and cinnamon. It’s often flavored with rose water or kewra and garnished with nuts like almonds or pistachios.

title: Pak Cuisines
text:
3.1 Tea






Pakistani Chai is a strong black tea typically made with black tea leaves, milk, sugar, and a blend of spices like cardamom, ginger, and cinnamon.
